Eerste zin van standaardmail is het onderwerp.
Standaardmail mag alleen spaties en newlines hebben. Tab en meerdere spaties wordt een spatie.
[FULLNAME] wordt vervangen door de gebruikersnaam.
[SERVERNAME] wordt vervangen door de servernaam

custommails houdt custom mails in
username customemail
formaat.

Mail_Controller:
Controleert of een process meerdere GPUs Claimt (1) of
Een process al langer dan een uur draait (2)
en laat de mailer een gepast mailtje verzenden met 
een notificatie en instructies.

exceptions:
een file kan worden toegevoegd die usernames bevat
die niet gemailt hoeven te worden



Rules:
Format is as follows:
[GROUP] [TIME] [NUMBER] [INTERVAL] [CUSTOM] [ISSUENO]

Group is a list of student numbers in the 'Groups' file under a 'GROUP X' header.
The X = [GROUP]
This is the list of people this rule applies to.
Alternatively, [GROUP] can be ALL, and in that case it applies to everyone.

[TIME] is a threshold for the amount of time that needs to have passed since the program was created.
In seconds.

[NUMBER] is the threshold for the number of GPUs the program is using.
If, for example, 8, then the program needs to use 8 GPUs to violate the rule.

Both [TIME] and [NUMBER] can be set to 0 to be irrelevant, so rules that use only [TIME] or only [NUMBER] as criterion can be created.

[INTERVAL] determines how much time needs to be between violation-emails for violators of this rule.

[CUSTOM] is an easily customizable variable that will be passed to the mailer, also as [CUSTOM].
It can be used to have one template mail where, for example, only the link to the website is changed.

[ISSUENO] determines which standard mail is sent.
